> **Amendment (2026-07-11, after exp002–exp007).** The experimental series
> reached its closing experiment on 2026-07-11 with two verdicts that end the
> series without a clean close. The geometric honesty criterion H11 — that
> φ-codebook quantization error is bounded by `(1−1/φ)/2 × |v|` — earned
> METRIC-DEFECT: ORACLE-PHI (perfect calibration) itself violates the
> criterion for ~25% of values, because the correct bound is
> `(1−1/φ)/2 × s_j` (half the shell gap, where `s_j > v`), not
> `(1−1/φ)/2 × |v|` (a strictly smaller quantity). The promise is real; the
> formula as written understates it. The ghost-flag fix H12 — that setting the
> mid-return countdown to K+4 on rebirth (rather than max with the
> formula-clock value) would collapse S4 coverage from 26.8% to < 2% —
> was FALSIFIED: coverage dropped only to 24.5%/10.9%, because the dominant
> source of mid-return flags is continuous natural steady-state deviations
> (~1.8% trigger rate × ~10 block average) that the rebirth-reset does not
> address, not the cold-start formula clock that was targeted. All prior
> regressions passed at their fifth confirmations. One targeted follow-up
> freeze is permitted for the ghost-fix mechanics only; the geometric criterion
> is not restated — its failure goes in Architecture Note 02 as-is. The series
> is suspended, not closed.
>
> **Amendment (2026-07-11, closing audit — decision rule).** A steward's
> audit was run before choosing between closing the series (Path A) and
> opening the permitted exp007b follow-up. Rule frozen before computation:
> Lift = E_f/E_u ≥ 2.0 AND sensitivity = 100% → CLOSE; Lift < 1.25 →
> OPEN exp007b. Replay SHA-256 matched 8c7757cb… exactly (bit-identical).
> Result: pooled Lift = 1.0006; S4 sensitivity = 66.7% (cold-start block
> t=0 missed — it carries no clock at t=0, state not yet ready). The max-
> relative-error structural floor of the phi-codebook (~99.7% of blocks
> reach rel-err ≈ 1.0 from near-zero values snapping to 0) is identical
> in flagged and unflagged groups, making the register's information
> content indistinguishable from zero. Path A was blocked by both
> conditions. Decision: **OPEN exp007b** (§2 ghost-fix mechanics only).
> A register that wakes on 12.4% of stationary blocks without distinction
> from genuine transients is an unkept register.
>
> **Amendment (2026-07-11, exp007b — final verdicts).** The permitted
> follow-up experiment (ghost-fix mechanics only) ran to completion on
> 2026-07-11. SHA-256 8c7757cb… matched bit-identically (the mid-return
> flag does not enter the state path, so the hash is stable across
> trigger variants). All sixth-confirmation regressions PASSED: S1 tie,
> displacement ≡ 0 (sixth), H2-f grid ±8% (sixth), H8a/H8b/H8c/H8d,
> H9 truthfulness, S4a. Three claims decided:
>
> H12-b (S4 coverage < 2%) — **PASS.** Collapsed from 24.5%/10.9% to
> 0.24%/0.24% (both distributions). Mechanism: infancy 3 blocks + rebirth-
> settle 7 blocks = 10 blocks exactly. Zero persistence triggers fired at
> steady state in 4096 blocks. The grammar works: K-consecutive filter
> kills the noise floor completely.
>
> H13 (S1 noise floor < 0.5%) — **PASS.** Collapsed from 12.4% to 0.073%
> (both distributions). Pure infancy (t=0,1,2 = 3 blocks). No persistence
> trigger fired on stationary data. The arithmetic on record was right:
> 1.8%³ ≈ 6×10⁻⁶ per block is undetectable in 4096 blocks.
>
> H14 (sensitivity = 100%) — **FALSIFIED** (both distributions). S4: 3/3
> = 100% ✓ (infancy covers the t=0 miss from the closing audit). S3↑: N/A
> (all excluded — strangers + settle). S3↓: 0/2 = 0% — blocks t=2048 and
> t=2049 are non-stranger, non-settle, and NOT flagged. The persistence gate
> requires K=3 consecutive blocks, but the REGIME rebirth fires at exactly
> the K-th block (t=2050), consuming the third count before the persistence
> trigger can fire. The gate's grammar — "K observations to build a case" —
> and the regime's grammar share the same K, creating a structural blind spot
> of exactly K−1=2 blocks at every step-DOWN transition. The watchman cannot
> sleep through nothing: it sleeps through the two blocks before it wakes.
>
> **Series closes here.** H14 FALSIFIED sends the MID-RETURN register to
> Architecture Note 02 §2 (funerals and costs) with its measured numbers.
> The follow-up permission does not renew. Deliverable: Architecture Note 02.
>
> **Post-series gap analysis (2026-07-11, exploratory — no verdict).** After
> closing, the H14 gap was measured, not reopened. The two missed blocks
> (t=2048, t=2049 on S3↓) were never invisible to the machine: the regime
> counter itself held the evidence — counter=1 at t=2048, counter=2 at
> t=2049. The deviation was already counted; the MID-RETURN register simply
> never read the counter. The simple road — raise MID-RETURN on any
> non-stranger block whose regime counter is nonzero — was measured against
> the sworn exp007b data (offline counter reconstruction matched every
> REGIME rebirth exactly): stationary + drift cost = 0 blocks in 8192
> (the counter runs on D≈2.0 shells, a far deeper tail than the noise
> threshold ≈0.75); S3↓ hypothetical sensitivity 2/2 = 100%, both
> distributions; S4 unchanged at 100%; hypothetical coverage would still
> sit at 0.073% (S1) and 0.244% (S4), far inside the frozen bounds. The
> three-state Watchman alternative is dominated: at p=1 it reopens the
> 1.8% floor H13 closed; at p=2 it shrinks the gap to one block but does
> not close it, and it adds a state machine. The H14 falsification was a
> wiring gap, not a grammar failure — the watchman was awake; nobody read
> his ledger. This analysis earns no verdict. The series remains CLOSED.
> If the counter-visible trigger is ever to be sworn, it requires a new
> pre-registration outside this series, judged fresh.
